examples.en: The camping trip was spoiled by bad weather.
Those kids were spoiled rotten by their mother.
The whole park is spoiled by litter.
His mother spoiled him, indulging his every whim.
She spends her time frivolously enjoying the easy life of a rich and spoiled girl.
The child was spoiled by overindulgence.
A trip in one point would have spoiled all.
You have spoiled them by your condescensions.
He was the favorite, and his mother spoiled him rotten.
If the tin can is blown, throw it away  the food inside is spoiled.
I spoiled the sauce by adding too much garlic.
This spoiled an otherwise excellent piece of work.
Responsibility turned the spoiled playboy into a driving young executive.
All that talk about taking up the farming life was just a lot of spoiled applesauce.
Ben was a spoilt brat (=a spoiled and unpleasant child).
The weather report warned that the holiday weekend would be spoiled by inclement weather.
